import pandas as pd
# Merge the sales and features datasets on 'Store' and 'Date'
sales_features = pd.merge(sales, features, on=['Store', 'Date', 'IsHoliday'])

# Merge the resulting dataset with the stores dataset on 'Store'
integrated_data = pd.merge(sales_features, stores, on='Store')

# Display the first few rows of the integrated dataset
print("Integrated Data:\n", integrated_data.head())
# Write the integrated dataset to a CSV file
integrated_data.to_csv('integrated_data.csv', index=False)

Hadoop Script

Providing necessary permissions

chmod +x mapper.py

chmod +x reducer.py

chmod +x run_hadoop_job.sh

!/bin/bash

Define variables

INPUT_FILE="/user/media/sales_data.csv"

HDFS_INPUT_DIR="/user/media"

HDFS_OUTPUT_DIR="/user/media/output"

MAPPER_SCRIPT="mapper.py"

REDUCER_SCRIPT="reducer.py"

Upload scripts and data to HDFS

hdfs dfs -put $INPUT_FILE $HDFS_INPUT_DIR/sales_data.csv

hdfs dfs -put $MAPPER_SCRIPT $HDFS_INPUT_DIR/$MAPPER_SCRIPT

hdfs dfs -put $REDUCER_SCRIPT $HDFS_INPUT_DIR/$REDUCER_SCRIPT

Set executable permissions for the scripts

hdfs dfs -chmod +x $HDFS_INPUT_DIR/$MAPPER_SCRIPT

hdfs dfs -chmod +x $HDFS_INPUT_DIR/$REDUCER_SCRIPT

Run the Hadoop Streaming job

hadoop jar /usr/lib/hadoop/hadoop-streaming.jar
-input $HDFS_INPUT_DIR/sales_data.csv \ -output $HDFS_OUTPUT_DIR
-mapper $HDFS_INPUT_DIR/$MAPPER_SCRIPT
-reducer $HDFS_INPUT_DIR/$REDUCER_SCRIPT

Retrieve the results

hdfs dfs -cat $HDFS_OUTPUT_DIR/part-00000

Running Script

./run_hadoop_job.sh

from pyspark.sql import SparkSession
from pyspark.sql.functions import col, avg, weekofyear, year, sum as _sum, lag, when
from pyspark.sql.window import Window
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import seaborn as sns
from pyspark.ml.clustering import KMeans
from pyspark.ml.feature import VectorAssembler
from pyspark.sql import functions as F

# Initialize Spark session
spark = SparkSession.builder.appName("AdvancedRetailDataAnalysis").getOrCreate()

# Convert pandas dataframe to Spark dataframe
spark_df = spark.createDataFrame(integrated_data)

# Extract year and week of year from Date column
spark_df = spark_df.withColumn('Year', year('Date'))
spark_df = spark_df.withColumn('WeekOfYear', weekofyear('Date'))

# Calculate weekly sales per store
weekly_sales = spark_df.groupBy('Store', 'Year', 'WeekOfYear').agg(_sum('Weekly_Sales').alias('Total_Weekly_Sales'))

# Calculate year-over-year sales growth
window_spec = Window.partitionBy('Store', 'WeekOfYear').orderBy('Year')
weekly_sales = weekly_sales.withColumn('Prev_Year_Sales', lag('Total_Weekly_Sales').over(window_spec))
weekly_sales = weekly_sales.withColumn('YoY_Growth', when(col('Prev_Year_Sales').isNotNull(),(col('Total_Weekly_Sales') - col('Prev_Year_Sales')) / col('Prev_Year_Sales')).otherwise(None))

# Sales forecasting (simple moving average)
window_spec_avg = Window.partitionBy('Store').orderBy('Year', 'WeekOfYear').rowsBetween(-3, 0)
weekly_sales = weekly_sales.withColumn('Moving_Avg', avg('Total_Weekly_Sales').over(window_spec_avg))

# sample the data it's too large
weekly_sales_sampled = weekly_sales.sample(fraction=0.1, seed=42)

# Convert Spark dataframe to Pandas dataframe for visualization
weekly_sales_pd = weekly_sales_sampled.toPandas()

# Plot weekly sales trends for a sample of stores
plt.figure(figsize=(12, 6))
sns.lineplot(x='WeekOfYear', y='Total_Weekly_Sales', hue='Store', data=weekly_sales_pd)
plt.xlabel('Week of Year')
plt.ylabel('Total Weekly Sales')
plt.title('Weekly Sales Trends for Sample Stores')
plt.legend(title='Store')
plt.show()

# Plot year-over-year growth trends for a sample of stores
plt.figure(figsize=(12, 6))
sns.lineplot(x='WeekOfYear', y='YoY_Growth', hue='Store', data=weekly_sales_pd)
plt.xlabel('Week of Year')
plt.ylabel('Year-over-Year Growth')
plt.title('Year-over-Year Growth Trends for Sample Stores')
plt.legend(title='Store')
plt.show()

# Plot moving average of weekly sales for a sample of stores
plt.figure(figsize=(12, 6))
sns.lineplot(x='WeekOfYear', y='Moving_Avg', hue='Store', data=weekly_sales_pd)
plt.xlabel('Week of Year')
plt.ylabel('Moving Average of Weekly Sales')
plt.title('Moving Average of Weekly Sales for Sample Stores')
plt.legend(title='Store')
plt.show()

# Stop Spark session
spark.stop()

import seaborn as sns
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

# Convert 'IsHoliday' to numeric (0 for False, 1 for True)
integrated_data['IsHoliday'] = integrated_data['IsHoliday'].astype(int)

# Select only numeric columns for correlation matrix
numeric_cols = integrated_data.select_dtypes(include='number').columns
corr_matrix = integrated_data[numeric_cols].corr()

# Plot heatmap of correlation matrix
plt.figure(figsize=(10, 8))
sns.heatmap(corr_matrix, annot=True, cmap='coolwarm', fmt='.2f', square=True)
plt.title('Correlation Matrix')
plt.show()
